| 2 | PII (email addresses) exposed without authentication/authorization | High | A01: Broken Access Control / A02: Cryptographic Failures (data exposure) |
| 3 | No rate limiting / DoS protection | Medium | A04: Insecure Design |
| 4 | No CORS policy defined explicitly | Low-Medium | A05: Security Misconfiguration |
| 5 | No request logging / monitoring | Medium | A09: Security Logging & Monitoring Failures |
| 6 | Listens on all interfaces by default (`app.listen(3000)`) | Low | A05: Security Misconfiguration |
| 7 | No graceful error handler — uncaught errors leak stack traces | Medium | A05 + A09 |
| 8 | Hardcoded port, no HTTPS/TLS termination guidance | Low | A02 |
| 9 | No `express.json()` size limits set (future-proofing) | Low | A04 |

