| # | Finding | Severity | OWASP Category |
|---|---------|----------|----------------|
| 1 | Sensitive PII (email addresses) returned without AuthN/AuthZ | High | A01 Broken Access Control / A04 Insecure Design |
| 2 | No authentication or session middleware | High | A07 Identification & AuthN Failures |
| 3 | Missing security headers (no Helmet) | Medium | A05 Security Misconfiguration |
| 4 | No rate limiting on any endpoint | Medium | A04 Insecure Design |
| 5 | CORS not configured (defaults are permissive if later added ad-hoc) | Medium | A05 Security Misconfiguration |
| 6 | No input validation / body parser limits | Medium | A03 Injection / A04 |
| 7 | `console.log` used for logging; no structured logging or request IDs | Low | A09 Logging & Monitoring Failures |
| 8 | No global error handler — stack traces may leak via default Express handler | Medium | A05 / A09 |
| 9 | Hard-coded port, no config management, `app.listen` runs on require | Low | A05 |
| 10 | No HTTPS / TLS termination guidance | Low | A02 Cryptographic Failures |
| 11 | `x-powered-by: Express` header leaks framework fingerprint | Low | A05 |
| 12 | No dependency manifest (`package.json` missing) — can't audit deps | Info | A06 Vulnerable Components |

