### 1. Sensitive data exposure on `/users` (OWASP A01: Broken Access Control + A02: Cryptographic Failures / Sensitive Data)
**`app.js:11-16`** — The `/users` endpoint returns PII (emails) with **no authentication, no authorization, and no rate limiting**. Even if the data is currently seeded/fake, this is the shape of the #1 most-exploited API vulnerability (BOLA/excessive data exposure, OWASP API Top 10 #1 & #3).

**Fix:** require auth, and return only fields the caller is entitled to.
```js
const requireAuth = (req, res, next) => {
  const token = req.headers.authorization?.replace(/^Bearer\s+/i, '');
  if (!token || !isValidToken(token)) return res.sendStatus(401);
  req.user = decodeToken(token);
  next();
};

app.get('/users', requireAuth, (req, res) => {
  const users = getUsers(); // from a real store
  // Strip PII unless caller has the right scope
  const safe = users.map(u => req.user.scopes.includes('users:read:pii')
    ? u
    : { id: u.id, name: u.name });
  res.json(safe);
});
